  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving child nutrition, children&apos;s rights and livelihood opportunities for young people</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2018, CAFOD will support a pilot project with Fundaci&#xF3;n Nuna to support work on child nutrition, children&#x2019;s rights and improving livelihood opportunities for young people. We would like to enrich support to the communities in Ancoraimes and Curva by using the model successfully implemented by CIPCA of employing a nutritionist to accompany families as part of the agricultural production training and support.  Nuna is keen to link work with children on nutrition in schools with awareness raising in schools about children&#x2019;s rights.  Nuna staff work in close contact with communities and are very aware of issues around gender and violence that affect children.  Nuna will begin with training on children&#x2019;s rights and nutrition to build relationships with the community and lay the foundations for engaging later on these sensitive subjects.

Fundaci&#xF3;n Nuna staff have observed that in these regions, that the only future young people can see for themselves is to migrate to the cities and they frequently express a lack of interest in farming.  Simultaneously, Nuna have noted that older participants in their projects are less interested in transforming their produce into commercial products such as biscuits, bread, dried meats and diary produce (cheese, yoghurt etc).  As part of this pilot project, Nuna will work with a small group of young people to train them to transform the produce produced by their families with a view to providing future training on markets and commercialisation.  The pilot will offer young people greater economic opportunities in a situation where they have little access to land and enable them to work together with their families at a time when most young people are leaving their families and communities.</narrative>
  </description>
